The project maintains a single Postman collection.

Location:
`docs/postman/collection.json`

## Structure

- Each module must have its own top-level folder inside the collection.
- Each resource/entity within a module must have its own sub-folder.
- All API endpoints must be added to the appropriate module folder.

## Variables

- Must use Postman variables for tokens and base URLs (e.g. `{{base_url}}`, `{{auth_token}}`).
- Never hardcode token values or base URLs directly in requests.
- The `auth_token` variable must be set by running the login/token request; document this in the collection description.

## Requests

- All requests must include `Accept: application/json` header.
- Requests with a body must include `Content-Type: application/json` header.
- Requests that support payloads (`POST`, `PUT`, `PATCH`, and `DELETE` when applicable) must include an example request body.
- Do not add placeholder/dummy bodies for body-less requests.

## Responses

- Each request must include at least one saved example response (success case).
- Error response examples (422, 403, 404) must be added where relevant.
- Any change to a request or response shape must be reflected here.
